<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>green man • greensman</xh5><p> <i>green man—</i>1. a symbol of a walking figure illuminated green on some pedestrian crossings: When the <u>green man</u> shows and the traffic has stopped, you can cross. 2. <i>(dated)</i> an inexperienced man or sailor: I am afraid we would have killed a <u>green man</u>, traveling and working as we did. 3. commissionaires working outside Harrods <i>(the fashionable London retail store):</i> Two traditionally dressed Harrod’s “<u>Green Men</u>” greeted guests at the entrance.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>little green men</b>—1. <i>mysterious extra-terrestrial beings of science fiction: </i>Her story of being kidnapped by <u>little green men</u> was sheer absurdity. 2. <i>pulsars (stars detected by pulsating radio signals only):</i> An entirely novel kind of star was referred to by astronomers as LGM (<u>Little Green Men</u>).</p><p><i>greensman</i>—(Movie Production) a member of the crew who decorates the ground with grass, flowers, etc. on an environment used for filming: <u>Greensmen</u> with water trucks began work a month before the shooting crew.</p> </entry>
